originalText: sgs_newton
Start Element
newton
I'm not a wussy!
$(context.player.Name)?
::A smiling face greets you.:: $(context.player.Name)! Thank you very much for saving my life. I owe you for that one.

::A terrified man leaps out of the dark corner and begins slashing the air in front of him. His shirt and pants are stained with blood, and you see a piece of cloth tied around his thigh below which a large wound grins at you. An instant passes, and the man retracts his knife and stares at you. 

A sigh of relief precedes his words.::

Aaaaah, you're not a psi bug. Thank goodness. I almost had a heart attack...
Did you kill them all?
When Tanner disappears, then everyone's asking questions; when I disappear - meh.
Cheers, $(context.player.Name).
Saved anyone else lately?
Vencel recommended I try Arlene's cooked psi bugger meat. Is he a moron or what?
Did you hear? The Faceless are gone! Cheers!
I heard you went to GMS. How'd it go?
Yeah, cool. I survived the psi buggers so that the Faceless can finish me. Dang.
$(context.player.Name). ::Raises a glass.::
context.npc_sgs_newton_pissed
You're back. Bummer. And I am not a wussy.
Leave me alone. I'm not a wussy, damn it!
l5
I am not a wussy!
::A smiling face greets you.:: $(context.player.Name)! Thank you very much for saving my life. I never got to thank you properly.
I apologize, you're not. I don't even know why I said that.
Yes, you are. Wussy!
I just came over to check out how you were doing. And be careful next time you go chasing hoppers. Bye.
context.npc_sgs_newton_metSecondTime
They're all dead. Let's get you out of here.
I think they're all dead. The path should be clear.
Not yet, I'll be back.
What can you tell me about this place?
Oh, you're the wussiest wuss in existence. One wuss to rule them all.
I'm sorry about that. I'm never going to call you a wussy again.
Oh. Good. I need to rest now. If you'd leave me alone now, please.
No, I'm--

I'm fine at the moment. The leg kinda still hurts, but, like, it's getting better. As far as hunting those stupid hoppers, that's not gonna happen *any* time soon. See you around, $(context.player.Name).
Wha--?
Are you Newton? Big Bret sent me out to look for you. You've been out of SGS for a while now.
I won't disturb you. Goodbye.
psiBeetles
loc_mushroomCoveBase_killedAllBugs
Great! GREAT! I wanna get the *hell* outta here as soon as possible. ::He rushes past you, dragging his injured leg behind him.::
Come on! Please hurry up!
Wh--What's frickin' wrong with you!? Please help me get out of here!

You-- ::Rage radiates from him, yet despite that he still doesn't manage to look threatening.:: That's it, you, you stupid *rock-for-brains*. You and I, we're not talking any more! Yes, you saved my life, and I am thankful, but I am not a wussy. I am *not* a wussy!
You swear?
How are you feeling, man?
::Leave.::
Yes, yes! I'm Newton. Don't even mention Big Bret to me. He sent me to catch those stupid hoppers. I guess I went too far to the west and ran into psi-bugs. He never told me about them!
What!? No, no, no - don't leave me here! Are you derailed!? You from SGS?
context.loc_mushroomCoveBase_deadPsiBugs
::Wait for him to limp away.::
Go scrub your colon with a stalagmite! Leave me alone!
Yes.
Wussy.
Better. The leg's still hurting from time to time, but I'll soon be as good as new-ton. ::He laughs.:: As you can see, I'm kinda relaxing here with the rest.
Why didn't you run away?
Yes I am. $(context.player.Name)'s the name. Are you Newton? Big Bret sent me out to look for you. You've been out of SGS for a while now.
Mc_NewtonLeaves
Okay. We are good. You saved my life and will not call me a wussy again. We are good.
You do that. Take care of yourself.

I did! I started running... around. Hey, the bugs surrounded me! I ended up in this plac-- ::He clenches his teeth in pain.:: Aaahhhh... and I cut my leg somewhere along the way. I stopped the stupid bleeding, but I can barely walk.
Thanks. I will. Cheers!
Why the hell are we still talking? Can you get rid of all those damn bugs so I can safely get outta here? I can't run and I most certainly can't fight.
Yeah, sure. I'll be back once the road is clear.
You are a bigger hopper than the ones you were sent to catch, but I'll see what I can do.
Don't take too long. I'll wait here.
Hopper? That was uncalled for. I'm frickin' wounded, $(#man/woman)! ::He grabs his leg.:: Aaah... I'll wait here.
